Sorbus domestica

   [9942.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Rosales:Rosaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names serviceberry, service tree, beam tree, checker tree,
   speierling, sorveira, sorveira brava, pau-vaca
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 9942

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: A deciduous or evergreen tree up to 15 m in height, with
   panicles of white flowers up to 10 cm long in late spring, followed by
   an abundance of pear or apple-shaped fruits on mature trees. Unusual
   orange-brown scaly bark. USE: The fruit needs to be stored until soft
   before use. GROWING PERIOD: Perennial. COMMON NAMES: Servant tree.
   FURTHER INF: It originates from Southern Europe, western Asia and
   northern Africa.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
